The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, April 13: The State Bank of India today extended its special home and car loans scheme by another five months till September 30. The bank had introduced a special scheme to provide home and car loans at 8 per cent and 10 per cent, respectively, in February. At that time the offer was till April 30.                             
	 New Delhi, April 13: Sebi today imposed a 30 per cent ceiling on the resources a mutual fund can invest in the debt instruments of a single entity. The move will help asset managers to diversify risks.                             
	 Mumbai, April 13: Reliance Petroleum has said its shareholders and creditors have approved the merger of RPL with Reliance Industries. Ninety-nine per cent of shareholders voted in favour of the merger in the meeting held on April 9.                                                                                                                           
